description: Under this scheme, financial assistance is provided to workers employed in industrial and commercial establishments in Haryana based on their percentage of disability, whether the disability occurs due to an accident or other reasons inside or outside the workplace.

name: Banglashree for Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises: Subsidy for Patent Registration (PRS)
description: “Subsidy for Patent Registration (PRS)” incentives under “Banglashree for MSMEs” scheme implemented by the MSMEs Dept., Government of West Bengal, aims to provide reimbursement of expenditure incurred for obtaining Patent Registration.

name: Award of Scholarships to Outstanding NCC Cadets of the UT of Puducherry
description: The scheme aims to recognize and support outstanding NCC cadets. The scheme offers scholarships to eligible candidates in various divisions: Senior Division Boys (Up to graduation), Senior Wing Girls, Junior Division Boys (Up to 12th Standard), and Junior Wing Girls.

name: Sewing Machine Scheme (HBOCWWB)
description: This scheme aims to encourage registered women construction workers and to enable them to mend their clothing at their homes. Under this scheme, financial assistance is provided to registered women construction workers to purchase a Sewing Machine.

name: Financial Assistance for Miscarriage for the Construction Workers
description: "Financial Assistance for Miscarriage for the Construction Workers" by the Delhi Building and Other Construction Workers Welfare Board, Labour Department, Delhi, is a welfare scheme that provides an amount of ₹3,000/- as financial assistance in case of miscarriage.

name: Marriage Assistance to Normal Persons Marrying Orthopedically Differently Abled Persons
description: The scheme 'Marriage Assistance to Normal Persons Marrying Orthopedically Differently Abled Persons' was launched by the Department for the Welfare of Differently Abled Persons, Government of Tamil Nadu. The scheme aims to provide marriage assistance to a normal person.

name: Satyvadi Raja Harishchandra Marnotar Sahay Yojana
description: The scheme was launched in the year 2000 to provide financial assistance to scheduled caste families at the time of the death of a family member to cover funeral expenses, due to their poor economic conditions.

name: Shednet House
description: The Shednet House provided subsidies to farmers so they could earn more income by cultivating horticultural crops like vegetables, flowers, fruits, etc. by controlling the agro-climatic factors, temperature, humidity, and sunlight.

name: Vermicompost Ikai
description: In the Vermicompost Ikai scheme, provide subsidies to farmers and Organic fertilizer is a systematic pest-nutrition process in which the soil is made fertile by absorbing other organic substances present within the soil.

name: Chief Minister Higher Education Scholarship Scheme
description: The scheme was launched by the Higher Education Department, Government of Rajasthan. This scheme aims to enhance educational levels and provide scholarship to children from low-income families.

name: The Tripura Tribal Folk Arts & Cultural (Financial Assistance) Rules, 2022
description: The Tripura Tribal Folk Arts & Cultural (Financial Assistance) Scheme, 2022, is a government initiative to provide financial assistance to the government and non-government organizations to promote & preserve the traditional culture programme, exhibition in different tribal communities, & folk songs

name: Pathari Kshetr Talab Nirman Aadharit Matsya Paalan ki Yojana
description: The "Pathari Kshetr Talab Nirman Aadharit Matsya Paalan ki Yojana" aims to promote fisheries by constructing ponds and setting up related supporting units in plateau-dominated districts. The initiative is designed to create new employment opportunities and provide a means of livelihood for farmers.

name: Dr. Bhim Rao Ambedkar Meritorious Student Award Scheme
description: This scheme awards special prizes to meritorious Scheduled Caste students who secure the highest marks in the Class 10th and 12th board examinations conducted by the Board of Secondary Education, CBSE, and ICSE in the state.

name: Funeral Expenses for the Construction Workers
description: The “Funeral Expenses for the Construction Workers” scheme by the BOCW Welfare Board, Labour Department,West Bengal, is a welfare scheme that provides financial assistance for funeral expenses to the nominees of a deceased registered member.

name: Jharkhand Krishi Rin Mafi Yojana
description: The objective of the scheme is to provide relief from the debt burden to short-term agricultural loan holders in the state. Under this scheme, outstanding loan amounts of up to ₹50,000/- in standard crop loan outstanding accounts as of 31st March 2020, will be waived.

name: Financial assistance for Marriage for the Construction Worker
state: The Dadra And Nagar Haveli And Daman And Diu
description: The "Financial Assistance for Marriage for the Construction Workers'' by the BOCW Welfare Board, Labour Department,  U.T. Administration of DNH & DD, is a welfare scheme that provides financial assistance for marriage of self and for children (upto 2 children) of the building workers.

name: Investment Promotion Scheme (IPS) for MSME Sector: Assistance To Small And Medium Enterprises (SME) For Raising Of Capital Through SME Exchange
state: The Dadra And Nagar Haveli And Daman And Diu
description: “Assistance SME For Raising Of Capital Through SME Exchange” under the “Investment Promotion Scheme (IPS)” for MSME sector, implemented by the Dept. of Industries, U.T. Administration Of DNH & DD, aims to provide One-time assistance of expenditure incurred on raising of fund through SME Exchange.

name: Safai Karmakar Ke Bachche Hetu Chhatravrtti Yojana
description: Chhattisgarh State Government started a scheme "Safai Karmakar Ke Bachche Hetu Chhatravrtti Yojana" for unorganized worker on 11 March 2015.

name: Deen Dayal Divyangjan Pension Scheme - Assam
category: Social welfare & Empowerment,Banking,Financial Services and Insurance
description: The scheme "Deen Dayal Divyangjan Pension Scheme" was launched during 2018-19 by Social Welfare Department, Assam. The objective of the scheme is to provide a monthly pension of ₹1,000/- to each differently-abled person for taking care of their health.

name: Old Age Homes - Tamil Nadu
category: Social welfare & Empowerment,Health & Wellness,Housing & Shelter,Women and Child
description: The "Old Age Homes" was launched by the Social Welfare and Women Empowerment Department, Government of Tamil Nadu. This scheme is to bring qualitative improvement in the living standards of old people of the state.

name: Term Loan under NSKFDC- Haryana
description: Under this scheme, loans are provided to Safai Karamcharis & their dependents for any viable income-generating activities with a maximum cost of up to ₹15,00,000/- per beneficiary. The beneficiary should be between 18 & 55 years of age and should be either Safai Karamchari or his/her dependent.

name: Saraswati Vidya Yojana: Reimbursement of Fees for Diploma/Graduation and Post-Graduation Professional Courses
state: The Dadra And Nagar Haveli And Daman And Diu
description: “Reimbursement of Fees for Diploma/ Graduation and Post-Graduation Professional Courses'' under “Saraswati Vidya Yojana”, implemented by the Directorate of Education,  Of DNH & DD, aims to provide financial assistance to girl students pursuing higher education in professional courses.

name: Workers In Case Of Permanent Disablement-JKBOCWWB
description: The "Workers In Case of Partial Permanent Disablement" scheme by the JKBOCW Welfare Board, Labour Department, Jammu & Kashmir, provides financial assistance to registered Building and Other Construction (BOC) workers in the case of permanent disablement.

name: Mukhyamantri Alpsankhyak Rozgar Rinn Yojana
description: The objective of this scheme is to provide loans of up to ₹5,00,000/- at a simple annual interest rate of 5% to youths from minority communities (Muslim, Sikh, Christian, Buddhist, Jain, and Parsi) for generating employment.

name: Production Of Certified Seeds
description: The "Production of Certified Seeds" scheme, offers a subsidy to farmers for producing certified seeds of Pulses.

name: Arivu Education Loan Scheme
description: The "Arivu Education Loan Scheme," launched by the Minorities Welfare Department, Government of Karnataka, and implemented by the Karnataka Minorities Development Corporation, offers loans to students pursuing professional courses like MBBS, B.E., B.Tech., MBA, MCA, LLB, and others in various fields

name: Incentive for Purchase of Electric Scooter for the Daughter of a Registered Construction Worker (HBOCWWB)
description: Under this scheme, an incentive of ₹50,000/- or the actual ex-showroom price of electric scooter, whichever is lower, will be provided by the Board through e-RUPI to the daughter of a registered construction worker to facilitate her mobility while pursuing higher education.

name: The West Bengal Incentive Scheme: Subsidy for Quality Improvement
description: “Subsidy for Quality Improvement” incentives under the “WBIS” scheme aims to provide a reimbursement for the fixed capital investment expenditure incurred for quality improvement, modernization and installation of pollution control devices and for obtaining ISI/BIS/ISO certification.

name: Scheme of Extending Family Maintenance Grant to the Families of the Deceased Famous Artists
description: "Scheme of Extending Family Maintenance Grant to the Families of the Deceased Famous Artists" was launched by the Art and Culture Department, Government of Tamil Nadu. The objective of the scheme is to provide a one-time maintenance grant of ₹25,000/- to the families of deceased famous artists.

name: Mukhyamantri Aanchal Amrit Yojana
category: Social welfare & Empowerment,Health & Wellness,Women and Child
description: “Mukhyamantri Aanchal Amrit Yojana” is a social security scheme by the Department of Women Empowerment and Child Development, Government of Uttarakhand, that aims to reduce malnutrition among the children of the state through providing vitamin added food.

name: Lakshya Scheme
description: The "LAKSHYA" scheme was launched by the Directorate of Higher Education, Government of Tripura. The objective of the scheme is to provide financial support in the form of scholarships to permanent residents of Tripura who have cleared the Civil Services Examination (CSE) conducted by the UPSC.

name: Denture, Spectacles & Hearing Aid Scheme (P.B.O.C.W.W.B)
description: The "Denture, Spectacles & Hearing Aid Scheme'' by the BOCW Welfare Board, Department of Labour, Punjab, is a welfare scheme that provides financial aid to beneficiary construction workers & their families for denture, spectacles & hearing aid.

name: "Outstanding Exporter" under “Motivation of Entrepreneurs to Start Industries and Fiscal Assistance to Industries - State Awards to Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises”
description: "Outstanding Exporter" under “Motivation of Entrepreneurs to Start Industries and Fiscal Assistance to Industries - State Awards to Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises” by the Industries & Commerce Dept, Puducherry, awards the direct manufacture exporters that are exporting for 3 years.

name: "Assistance for Intellectual Property Protection Support" under "Motivation of Entrepreneurs to Start Industries and Fiscal Assistance to Industries - Various Incentives"
description: Through this scheme, assistance of 50% is provided subject to a maximum of ₹2,00,000/- for the expenditure for obtaining domestic patent (₹5,00,000/- for international patent). The applications are accepted offline in the prescribed form available on the Official Website of the Department.

name: Vidhva Vivah Uphar Yojana
description: The Rajasthan government's Social Justice and Empowerment Department launched the "Vidhva Vivah Uphar Yojana" program, a social welfare initiative that aims to improve the lives of widow women.

name: "Capital Investment Subsidy: Physically Handicapped Persons/ Ex-Servicemen" under "Motivation of Entrepreneurs to Start Industries and Fiscal Assistance to Industries"
description: Through this scheme, the new industrial units which started production on or after 5th August 2009 by physically handicapped entrepreneurs and Ex-Servicemen for the investments made on land, building and plant and machinery are eligible for capital investment subsidy at the rate of 25%.

name: Silicosis Pidit Hita-dhikariyon Hetu Sahayata Yojana
description: The Silicosis Affected Workers Welfare Scheme is an initiative launched by the Government of Rajasthan to provide financial assistance to workers suffering from silicosis and their families.

name: Vivah Sahayata Yojana - Madhya Pradesh
description: Under the labor department of Madhya Pradesh State, this scheme "Vivah Sahayata Yojana" was started in 2018.

name: Pension to Unmarried Poor, Incapacitated Women of Age 50 years and above
description: The 'Pension to Unmarried Poor, Incapacitated Women of age 50 years and above' was launched by the Social Welfare and Women Empowerment Department, Tamil Nadu. The scheme aims to provide a pension of ₹1,000/- to unmarried, poor, incapacitated women of age 50 years and above.

name: Unemployment Assistance Scheme - Tamil Nadu
description: In 2006, Tamil Nadu Government started Unemployment Assistance Scheme for the welfare of unemployed youth of  the state.

name: Cash Award (MBOCWWB)
description: Under the scheme, the Board annually awards cash prizes to three male and three female children of registered construction workers in each district who scores the highest marks in the SSLC examination.

name: National Award For Senior Citizens (Vayoshreshtha Samman): Lifetime Achievement
description: The "Lifetime Achievement Award" is conferred to eminent and outstanding senior citizens, preferably above seventy years, who have worked in the field of ageing and made significant contributions in the field, for the cause of elderly persons, especially indigent senior citizens.

name: National Award For Senior Citizens (vayoshreshtha Samman): Creative Art
description: The "Vayoshreshtha Samman: Creative Art" award shall be given to winners of National or international acclaim for their contribution to literature, theatre, cinema, music, dance, painting, sculpture, photography, etc. and who continue to be active in their field well into their old age. The awards a

name: Financial Assistance for Encouraging Worker's Children's Participation in Cultural Activities- Haryana Labour Welfare Board
tags: Financial Assistance,Worker,Participation In Cultural Activities,Artist,Cultural Competitions,Dance,Music
description: Under this scheme, financial assistance is provided to the children of the workers working in the industrial and commercial establishments of the state of Haryana for participating in cultural competitions so that the children of the workers can also become good artists.

name: MeitY Digital India Internship Scheme
description: An opportunity for a student to secure practical work experience under the guidance of a qualified and experienced Supervisor/Mentor in Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology (MeitY) in the form of Digital India Internship Scheme.

name: Funeral Assistance (HBOCWWB)
description: Under this scheme, the “Haryana Building & Other Construction Workers Welfare Board” (HBOCWWB) provides financial assistance for funeral expenses to the nominee or legal heir of a registered worker in the event of their death.

name: Uniform Allowance to the Wards of Ex-Servicemen/Widows (Sainik Welfare)
description: "Uniform Allowance to the Wards of Ex-Servicemen/Widows (Sainik Welfare)" is a Welfare Scheme by the Dept of Sainik Welfare, Puducherry. The wards of the ESM / Widows of ESM studying in Government-recognized Institutions are provided allowances towards purchase of their uniform.

name: Grant for the Purchase of Work Related Tools for the Construction Workers
description: "Grant for the Purchase of Work Related Tools for the Construction Workers" by the Delhi Building and Other Construction Workers Welfare Board, Labour Dept., Delhi, is a welfare scheme that provides an amount of ₹5,000/- as grant to the members of the Fund, for the purchase of work related tools.

name: Shubhshakti Yojana
description: The Shubshakti Yojana has been initiated by the Rajasthan government with the aim of providing financial assistance to regular construction workers, unmarried laborers, and their daughters.

name: ICRO Amrit Internship Programme
description: The IPL Centre for Rural Outreach (ICRO) has launched ICRO Amrit Internship Programme focused on youth productivity for prosperity. The interns will be placed at the headquarters and Regional Offices of NPC/ IPL. The duration of the internship will be 3 months initially, renewable up to four times.

name: Day Care - cum - Recreation Centre and Physiotherapy Unit
description: Through the scheme “Day Care - cum - Recreation Centre and Physiotherapy Unit" under "Grant-in-Aid to Pondicherry Society for the Care of the Aged (PONCARE)", the senior citizens are provided free physiotherapy given by the physiotherapist, as advised by the doctors.

name: Maintenance Allowance to Severely Affected Persons
description: The 'Maintenance Allowance to Severely Affected Persons' scheme was launched by the Department for the Welfare of Differently Abled Persons. The scheme aims to provide a maintenance allowance to the severely affected persons who cannot be rehabilitated by any other assistance.

name: Manav Garima Yojana
description: The scheme offers financial assistance to Scheduled Caste individuals who wish to establish cottage industries for self-employment without requiring bank loans. Employment/tool kits are provided to those who seek self-employment opportunities.

name: Cattle Shed Subsidy Scheme under Scheduled Castes Sub Plan (SC Category)
description: The scheme “Cattle Shed Subsidy Scheme under Scheduled Castes Sub Plan (SCSP)” is implemented by the Directorate of Animal Husbandry, Government of Gujarat. Under this scheme, the financial assistance is given to Scheduled Caste beneficiaries for construction of Cattle Shed for 2 animals.

name: Dr. Baba Saheb Ambedkar Loan for Higher Study in Foreign Countries
description: Under this scheme, a loan of ₹15 lakhs is provided at an interest rate of 4% to offer financial assistance to bright career students of the Scheduled Castes who cannot go abroad for higher studies due to the their poor economic condition.

name: Loan for the Purchase of Tools (GBOCWWB)
description: "Loan for the Purchase of Tools (GBOCWWB)" is a Welfare Scheme by the Goa Building and Other Construction Workers Welfare Board of the Dept of Labour and Employment, Govt of Goa. Through this scheme, the worker registered with the Board is provided with a loan of ₹5,000/- for the purchase of tools.

name: Mukhyamantri Samekit Chaur Vikas Yojana
description: The "Mukhyamantri Samekit Chaur Vikas Yojana" under Seven Nishchay-2, aims to develop undeveloped and unutilized private land in Bihar for fish-based integrated aquaculture. With a budget of ₹2972.79 lakh, the scheme targets the sustainable development of 600 hectares of Chaur land, enhancing fish.

name: Death Benefit (O.B.O.C.W.W.B)
tags: Labour,Building Worker,Construction Worker,Death Benefit,Accidental Death,Normal Death
description: The "Death Benefit'' scheme by the BOCW Welfare Board, Labour and Employment Department, Odisha, is a welfare scheme that provides financial assistance to the nominee(s) of the beneficiary as death benefit.

name: Death Benefit
tags: Labour,Building Worker,Construction Worker,Death Benefit,Accidental Death,Normal Death
description: The "Death Benefit'' scheme by the BOCW Welfare Board, Labour Department, West Bengal, is a welfare scheme that provides financial assistance to the nominee(s) of the beneficiary as death benefit.

name: Investment Promotion Scheme (IPS) for MSME Sector: Assistance For Patent Registration /Trade Mark Registration
state: The Dadra And Nagar Haveli And Daman And Diu
description: “Assistance For Patent Registration/ Trade Mark Registration” under the “Investment Promotion Scheme (IPS)” for MSME sector, implemented by the Dept. of Industries, U.T. Administration Of DNH & DD, aims to extend support for obtaining Patent Registration/ Trade Mark Registration.

name: Scheme for Establishment of Backyard Poultry Units
description: The objective of the scheme is to improve the socio-economic and nutritional status of the poor families, small farmers and landless agricultural labourers and other economically weaker section of the society.

name: Chief Minister Divyangjan Empowerment Scheme (Sambal)
description: The State government of Bihar launched the "Chief Minister Divyangjan Empowerment Scheme (Sambal) " scheme with the aim of improving the lives of Disable persons. Financial assistance is provided by the government through these schemes.

name: Sanction of Enhancement of Marriage Incentive Awards for Marriages Between Persons with Differently Abled and Normal Persons
description: The "Sanction of Enhancement of Marriage Incentive Awards for Marriages Between Persons with Differently Abled and Normal Persons" scheme aims to provide marriage incentive awards from ₹50,000/- to ₹1,00,000/- to encourage marriages between differently-abled persons and normal persons.

name: Education Loan Scheme (NSFDC)
tags: Education Loan,NSFDC,Student,Study In India,Study Abroad,Scheduled Caste
description: The scheme implemented by the National Scheduled Castes Finance & Development Corporation, Ministry of Social Justice & Empowerment, Govt. of India. Under this Scheme, loan is provided for pursuing full-time Professional/Technical courses in recognized institutions as one time assistance.

name: Biju Pucca Ghar Yojana
description: The government of Odisha is committed to providing Pucca houses to all the rural households living in Kutcha houses. State Government with a view to achieving this objective launched “Biju Pucca Ghar Yojana (BPGY)” during the year 2014.

name: Financial Assistance (Kanyadaan) on the Occasion of Marriage of Daughter- Haryana Silicosis Board
description: Under this scheme, financial assistance of ₹51,000/- is provided to workers suffering from silicosis, as confirmed by the Silicosis Diagnosis Board, Haryana, for the marriage of up to three of their daughters.

name: Shramyogi Home Town Scheme- Gujarat Labour Welfare Board
tags: Home Town,Payment Of Railway Fares,Migrant Labourers,Organized Worker
description: The objective of the scheme is to facilitate the payment of railway fares for migrant labourers employed in the organized sector in Gujarat, enabling them to travel to or from their home country to the nearest railway station.

name: Jal Hauj
description: The objective of the Jal Hauj scheme is to promote sustainable water management practices and address water scarcity issues by facilitating the construction of water harvesting structures.

name: Fawara Sanyantra
description: Under the Fawara Sanyantra Through this scheme, the government will provide subsidies to farmers to install sprinkler plants. This will save water and farmers will also be able to irrigate their fields through sprinklers.

name: Maternity Benefit Scheme (P.B.O.C.W.W.B)
description: The "Maternity Benefit Scheme'' by the BOCW Welfare Board, Department of Labour, Punjab, is a welfare scheme that provides financial assistance to the female construction workers and spouse of the male workers to support childbirth-related expenses maximum for two living children.

name: Labour Accident benefit Scheme- Gujarat Labour Welfare Board
description: Under the scheme, financial assistance is provided to workers (Shramyogis) who become disabled during their duty period due to an accident or any other reason at the working premises of the establishment.

name: Development and Maintenance of Orchard Cum Horti Nurseries
description: The scheme has been launched for the production and multiplication of good, high-yielding, diseased free planting materials in the Government farms for distribution to farmers through the District Horticulture Officer.

name: Disability Pension (A.B.O.C.W.W.B)
description: The Board provides financial assistance as disability pension to a beneficiary who is permanently disabled due to paralysis leprosy, TB., accident etc. in addition to this pension he/she will be eligible for an one time Ex-gratia payment depending upon the percentage of disability.

name: Educational Assistance (A.B.O.C.W.W.B)
description: The “Educational Assistance” scheme was started by the Assam Building and Other Construction Workers Welfare Board, Labour Welfare Department, Government of Assam to provide educational assistance to the children of the registered construction workers who are studying in Class I to Post Graduate.

name: Capital Investment Subsidy: Thrust Area Industries" under "Motivation of Entrepreneurs to Start Industries and Fiscal Assistance to Industries"
description: Throught the "Capital Investment Subsidy: Thrust Area Industries" scheme, the Thrust Area Industries are provided Subsidy on the Investments on Plant and Machinery. The applications are accepted offline in the prescribed form available on the Official Website of the Department.

name: Shramik Basera Yojana (GBOCWWB)
description: Under the scheme, the accommodation facilities will be provided @ ₹5/- per day to registered construction workers in temporary prefabricated housing with basic amenities that can be dismantled.

name: Nishaktata Pension Yojana (JBOCWWB)
category: Banking,Financial Services and Insurance,Social welfare & Empowerment
description: "Nishaktata Pension Yojana (JBOCWWB)" is a scheme by the Department of Labour, Employment, Training & Skill Development Govt of Jharkhand. The scheme provides a pension of ₹ 1,000/- per month to the registered beneficiary who is permanently disabled due to paralysis/leprosy/tuberculosis/accident.

name: Dr. D.S. Kothari Research Grant For Newly Recruited Faculty Members
description: The scheme "Dr. D.S. Kothari Research Grant for Newly Recruited Faculty Members" is a research grant scheme by the University Grants Commission (UGC), Department of Higher Education (DoHE). The purpose of the research grant is to provide opportunities to regularly appointed faculty members.

name: National Scheme of Apprenticeship Training
description: The primary goal of this scheme is to bridge the gap in practical experience for fresh Graduate Engineers, Diploma holders, and 10+2 Vocational pass-outs in approximately 10,000 industrial establishments. The apprentices undergo a one-year training period, receiving a monthly stipend.

name: Central Sector Scheme for Rehabilitation of Bonded Labourer
description: The scheme addresses eradicating bonded labour in India. It introduces varying rehabilitation assistance amounts based on beneficiary categories, such as adults, children, women, and extreme cases, with provisions for annuity schemes and Direct Benefit Transfer.

name: Palanhar Scheme
description: Palanhar Yojana has been started by the state government of Rajasthan to benefit the orphan and needy children of the state.

name: Medhavi Chhatr/Chhatra Shiksha Protsahan Yojana
description: Chhattisgarh state Government started a scheme "Medhavi Chhatr/ Chhatra Shiksha Protsahan Yojana" for education.

name: Pratibha Kiran Scholarship
description: Pratibha Kiran Scholarship has been launched by the Government of Madhya Pradesh. Through this scheme, scholarship will be provided every year to girl students living below the poverty line.

name: "Subsidy for Quality Certification" under "Motivation of Entrepreneurs to Start Industries and Fiscal Assistance to Industries - Various incentives"
description: "Subsidy for Quality Certification" under "Motivation of Entrepreneurs to Start Industries and Fiscal Assistance to Industries - Various incentives" is a scheme by the Industries and Commerce Dept, Puducherry. An assistance is granted for a maximum of 3 quality certifications @ 50% of the cost.

name: Maize Development through Cluster Approach Scheme
description: The objectives of the scheme is to increase food grain production in order to attain self-sufficiency by growing high yielding varieties of maize and also by adopting the crop and location specific production technology.

name: Khiladi Protsahan Yojana
description: In 2017, the Madhya Pradesh Labour Department initiated the Khilaadee Protsaahan Yojana to provide financial assistance to players.

name: Shiksha Protsaahan Puraskaar yojana
description: By the Labour Department of Madhya Pradesh, a scheme (Shiksha Protsahan Puraskar Yojana) was initiated for the financial assistance to the children.

name: National Award For Senior Citizens (Vayoshreshtha Samman): Best Private Sector Organisation In Promoting The Wellbeing And Welfare Of Senior Citizens
description: The "Vayoshreshtha Samman: Best Private Sector Organisation in Promoting the Wellbeing and Welfare of Senior Citizens" award shall be given to the Corporate Houses, addressing the problems of the elderly either by providing them gainful employment, utilising their skills and experience.

name: Financial Assistance to Widow/Dependent in case of Death of a Worker- Haryana Labour Welfare Board
description: Under this scheme, financial assistance of ₹2,00,000/- is given to the widow or dependent of the worker working in the industrial and commercial establishments of Haryana state in case of his death due to any reason.

name: Pashu Bima Yojana
description: The scheme 'Pashu Bima Yojna' was launched by the Directorate of Dairy Development, Government of Bihar. The scheme aims to provide insurance security to farmers against the financial loss caused by cattle death and to improve the rural economy.

name: Multimedia Training - Tamil Nadu
description: The Department for the Welfare of Differently Abled Persons, Government of Tamil Nadu, launched the "Multimedia Training Program" for people with locomotor and hearing impairments.

name: Fare for Visiting Home Town (HBOCWWB)
description: Under this scheme, a free traveling facility to visit the hometown once in a year for a family not exceeding 5 members is provided to the registered construction workers who have a minimum of two year’s regular membership of the Board.

name: Funeral Assistance for the Construction Workers
description: The "Funeral Assistance for the Construction Workers" by the Delhi Building and Other Construction Workers Welfare Board, Labour Department, Delhi, is a welfare scheme that provides funeral assistance of ₹10,000/- in case of death of a member to their nominees/dependents.

name: Yatra Pass in DTC non AC Buses for the Construction Workers
description: The "Yatra Pass in DTC non AC Buses for the Construction Workers" by the Delhi Building and Other Construction Workers Welfare Board, Labour Department, Delhi, is a welfare scheme that provides a pass of ₹ 2400/- per three months for non AC DTC bus to the registered workers for purchasing.

name: "Input Assistance to Farmers for Taking up Fish Farming in Farm Ponds" Component of the "Mukhyamantri Maschyajibi Kalyan Yojana" Scheme
description: The objective of this scheme is to increase the inland fish production, and to enhance the income of farmers in the State though aquaculture. Input assistance is provided to the farmers who have excavated farm ponds under MGNREGA for facilitating the production of fingerling and fish.

name: Plant Protection including Integrated Pest Management Scheme
description: The objective of the scheme is to mobilize and support farmers to use bio-pesticides and bio- agents for plant health management through distribution of bio-pesticides and other IPM tools and through sale of Sprayers and Plant Protection Equipment to encourage organic crop production.

name: Chief Minister Agriculture and Food Processing Scheme

description: The “Refund of Subscriptions for the Construction Workers” scheme by the BOCW Welfare Board, Labour Department, West Bengal, is a welfare scheme that provides reimbursement of the entire subscription, with 8% interest, to the beneficiary at age 60, after 3 years if they choose to leave the Board, or

name: Investment Promotion Scheme (IPS) for MSME Sector: Incentives For Doubling Of Export Values
state: The Dadra And Nagar Haveli And Daman And Diu
description: “Incentives For Doubling Of Export Values” under the “Investment Promotion Scheme (IPS)” for MSME sector, implemented by the Dept. of Industries, U.T. Administration Of DNH & DD, aims to extend support to MSMEs to increase exports and enhance export values.

description: Launched on 9th February 2024, "Mukhyamantri Sports Development Scheme - Unemployed Young Professional Sportsperson" was launched by the Directorate of Youth Affairs & Sports, Govt. of Tripura. The scheme aims to generate employment opportunities for young experienced professional sportspersons

name: One Time Cash Incentive towards acquiring BEd, BPEd, DTEd, PGDCA (Sainik Welfare)
description: "One Time Cash Incentive towards acquiring BEd, BPEd, DTEd, PGDCA" is a Welfare Scheme by the Armed Forces Flag Day Fund of the Department of Sainik Welfare, Puducherry. Through this scheme, up to ₹20,000/- is provided to the unemployed Ex-servicemen to pursue the mentioned programs/courses.

name: Pre-SSC Scholarship for Scheduled Caste Students (Parixitlal Majmudar Scholarship)
description: Under this scheme, scholarships are provided to Scheduled Caste students who are studying in Class 1 to 10 in Government/Grant-in-Aid Schools/Private Schools.

description: The objective of the scheme is to provide a subsidy for the purchase of a bicycle to laborers working in the organized sector, enabling them to commute between their residence and workplace.

name: Government Working Women’s Hostel

The scheme aims to provide safe accommodation facilities to working women who live far away from their families, belonging to lower and middle-income groups.

name: Pension Scheme for Grade II Deformed Leprosy Patients
description: The scheme "Pension Scheme for Grade II Deformed Leprosy Patients" is a Pension Scheme by the Directorate of Social Welfare and Social Education, Government of Tripura. The scheme provides financial assistance of ₹2,000/- per month to Leprosy Patients who are residents of Tripura.

The scheme is aimed at providing financial assistance to families belonging to the Scheduled Caste (SC) community in the state to help them become economically self-reliant.

description: The “Coconut Palm Insurance Scheme (CPIS)” is being implemented by the Coconut Development Board, Ministry of Agriculture and Farmers Welfare, Government of India with the objective of insuring coconut palms against natural calamities, climatic risks, pests, diseases and other perils.

The scheme is intended for providing Financial Grant for conducting a Study Tour of ATAL TUNNEL
by Students / faculty of AICTE approved Institutions in the field of technical education.

description: The scheme "AICTE - Grant for Augmenting Infrastructure in North Eastern Region (GAINER)" was introduced by AICTE to enhance the functional efficiency of the technical institutes located in far-flung areas of North East India, by addressing deficiencies in water, electricity, and internet.

It helps to address longevity risks among  workers in unorganized sector and encourages the workers to voluntarily save for retirement.

name: Medical Termination of Pregnancy Scheme (PULWS)

This margin money grants will reduce the initial financial burden on the entrepreneurs while availing term loan/working capital loan from the financial institutions for setting up of silk weaving units.

description:
AICTE e-Shodh Sindhu Scheme (eSS) provides subscriptions of e-Resources like Web of Science, Scopus,
ASME, ASCE and Bentham Science to institutions.

name: Mukyamantri Samuhik Vivah Evam Anudan Yojna
description: The Rajasthan Government to encourage the organization of mass marriages in the state, provide financial grants to reduce wastage in marriages,

description: an Education Loan scheme by the Ministry of Social justice and Empowerment for Safai Karamchari, Manual Scavengers, and their dependants aged 18 years and above.

name: Capital Investment Subsidy Scheme for Goan Diaspora

This scheme envisioned providing free cochlear implantation surgery for children in the age group of 0-5 years, who are hearing impaired.

name: Medical Assistance (GBOCWWB)
description: Through the "Medical Assistance (GBOCWWB)" scheme, the worker who is hospitalized for 5 or more days due to an accident or any disease is provided with ₹400/- for the first 5 days and ₹40/- for the remaining days, subject to a maximum ₹2,000/-.

name: Scheme for Supply of TV Sets to Industrial Establishments/Labour Welfare Centres/Clubs/Recreation Rooms
description: "Scheme for Supply of TV Sets to Industrial Establishments/Labour Welfare Centres/Clubs/Recreation Rooms" by the Dept of Labour and Employment, Goa aims to provide television sets to enable the workers/employees to witness programmes of nation national integration besides broadening their outlook.

name: Investment Promotion Scheme (IPS) for Textile Sector: Assistance Of Interest Subsidy For Textile Sector
state: The Dadra And Nagar Haveli And Daman And Diu
description: “Assistance Of Interest Subsidy For Textile Sector” under the “Investment Promotion Scheme (IPS)” for Textile Sector, implemented by the Dept. of Industries, U.T. Administration Of DNH & DD, aims to provide credit linked interest subsidy for Textile and Technical Textile sector.

name: Financial Assistance to Persons Suffering from Rare Diseases
description: The scheme “Financial Assistance to Persons Suffering from Rare Diseases” was launched by Social Justice & Empowerment Department, Govt. of Haryana. Under this scheme, financial assistance of ₹3000/- per month will be provided to all persons of Haryana domicile, who are suffering from Rare Diseases.

name: Scheme of Conferring ‘Kalaimamani’ Award
description: The "Scheme of Conferring ‘Kalaimamani’ Award - Tamil Nadu" was launched by the Art & Culture Dept. Tamil Nadu. The awards felicitate the famous artists who are serving in a commendable manner in the fields of Eyal, Isai, Natakam, Natyam, Cinema, Isai Natakam, Folk arts, Television & related arts.

name: Fellowship Scheme for M.Phil & Ph.D for Scheduled Caste Students (Maharaja Sayajirao Gayakvad Scholarship)
description: Under this scheme, Scheduled Caste students pursuing M.Phil and Ph.D. programs at any recognized universities will receive a monthly fellowship.

name: Mukhya mantri Krishak Udyami Yojana
description: The objective of this scheme is to provide financial assistance to the sons and daughters of farmers to establish their businesses. the government of Madhya Pradesh provided loans to the bank for all citizens of the state.

name: Prime Minister’s Scholarship Scheme for the Wards of States/UTs Police Personnel
description: The scheme was introduced by the Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India from the academic session 2019-20 to encourage higher technical & professional education for the dependent wards of States/UTs Police Personnel who are martyred during Terror/Naxal attacks.

name: Nanaji Deshmukh Krishi Sanjivani Prakalp
description: The project aims to enhance climate-resilience and profitability of smallholder farming systems in 15 project districts of Maharashtra through promotion of climate resilient technology and commodity value chain across approximately 5,000 drought-prone and/or sodicity/salinity affected villages.

name: CIFE - Institutional Fellowship
description: From the year 2010 onwards, the division is offering Masters and PhD in two disciplines namely Fish Nutrition and Feed Technology and Fish physiology and Biochemistry with an objective of moulding professionals with fundamental and advanced knowledge and expertise.

name: Subsidy Scheme For Purchase Of Taxi / Goods Vehicle / Passenger Autorickshaw
category: Banking,Financial Services and Insurance,Social welfare & Empowerment
description: Those beneficiaries who are sanctioned / approved for loan from the Banks for the purchase of Passenger Autorickshaw / Goods Vehicle / Taxi will be provided a subsidy of 33% of the value of the vehicle or a maximum subsidy of Rs. 2.5 Lakhs. Women will be given priority. Women will be given priority.

name: Banglashree for Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises: Subsidy for Work Force Welfare Assistance (WWAS)
description: “Subsidy for Work Force Welfare Assistance (WWAS)” incentives under “Banglashree for MSMEs” scheme implemented by the MSMEs Dept., Government of West Bengal, aims to provide reimbursement of expenditure incurred for paying contribution towards Employees State Insurance (ESI) and Employees Provident.

name: Deen Dayal Upadhyaya Bunkar Yojana
description: DDUBY is a government initiative in Arunachal Pradesh to provide affordable credit to women weavers, offering an interest subvention of 7% on short-term loans and working capital requirements.

name: Ex-gratia Payment for the Construction Workers
description: The "Ex-gratia Payment for the Construction Workers" by the Delhi Building and Other Construction Workers Welfare Board, Labour Department, Delhi, is a welfare scheme for the registered workers of the board that provides an ex-gratia amount of ₹1,00,000/- in case of permanent disability.

name: Arundhati Gold Scheme
description: The ARUNDHATI scheme started on January 1, 2020. It will offer 10 grams of gold as a gift to every bride. The bride and Bridegroom can apply for the scheme before the wedding. The scheme will cost about Rs 800 crore annually.

name: Rajasthan Chief Minister's Relief Fund - Medical Help
description: Rajasthan Chief Minister’s Relief Fund – medical help scheme launched on April 1999 under Chief Minister’s Relief Fund in Rajasthan for Individual for Non BPL whose family income should be at least 2lakhs per annum.

name: ICAR Senior Research Fellowship For Post-Graduate Studies In Agricultural Sciences
description: ICAR awards a certain number of Senior Research Fellowships for Ph.D. in an Agricultural University (AU), in different disciplines of agriculture and allied sciences. This is done to encourage talented students to undertake higher agricultural education.

name: Raw Material Assistance Scheme
description: Raw Material Assistance Scheme aims to help MSMEs by way of financing the purchase of Raw Material (Both indigenous & imported). This gives an opportunity to MSMEs to focus better on manufacturing quality products.

name: Kisan Samriddhi Yojana - Chhattisgarh
description: Chhattisgarh State Government started a scheme "Kisan Samriddhi Yojana" for farmer.

name: Soft Loan Scheme for Women Entrepreneurs
description: The scheme “Soft Loan Scheme for Women Entrepreneurs” was started under Kerala Startup Mission to support women startups with a soft loan of an amount limited to ₹15 Lakhs as working capital for implementing works & projects received from Govt. departments and Public Sector Undertaking in Kerala.

name: The Meghalaya Victim Compensation Scheme, 2022
description: The Meghalaya Victim Compensation Scheme, 2022 is a social welfare scheme introduced by the Social Welfare Department, Govt. of Meghalaya. Under this scheme, financial assistance to the victim along with support services such as shelter, counseling, medical aid, legal assistance, education, etc.

name: West Bengal Student Credit Card Scheme
description: The Higher Education Department, Government of West Bengal has introduced the Student Credit Card Scheme for the students of West Bengal to enable them to pursue higher education without having any financial constraints.

name: Assistance under SC/ST Prevention of Atrocities Act
description: The scheme “Assistance under SC/ST Prevention of Atrocities Act” was introduced by the Adi Dravidar Welfare Department, Government of Puducherry. The objective of the scheme is to provide immediate relief to the victims of atrocities who are from Scheduled Castes/ Scheduled Tribes.

name: Financial Assistance to Poor Scheduled Caste People Suffering From Prolonged Diseases
description: The scheme “Financial Assistance to Poor Scheduled Caste People Suffering From Prolonged Diseases” was introduced by the Adi Dravidar Welfare Dept, Govt of Puducherry. The objective of the scheme is to assist poor patients from Scheduled Castes suffering from prolonged illness.

name: Dr. Panjabrao Deshmukh Hostel Maintenance Allowance
tags: Dr. Panjabrao Deshmukh,Hostel Allowance,Education,Maharashtra Scheme,Student Scheme
description: This scheme is for the Students whose parent's annual Income is below 800000 and Students whose parents are Marginal Land Holder and registered laborers.

name: Delhi Ladli Scheme
description: Delhi Ladli Scheme was launched by the Department of Women & Children Development, Government of the National Capital Territory (NCT) of Delhi on 1st January 2008 to empower girl children born in Delhi. The State Bank Life Insurance Co. Ltd. (SBIL) is the scheme's Fund Manager.

name: Scheme For Working Women Hostel
description: A scheme to promote accommodation for working women, with day care facility for their children, wherever possible, in urban, semi urban, or even rural areas where employment opportunity for women exist.

name: SMILE - Comprehensive Rehabilitation For Welfare Of Transgender Persons – Skill Development And Training
description: The scheme aims to provide employment opportunities to the person belonging to transgender person community by providing them market-oriented skills.

name: Registration & Stamp Duty Subsidy Scheme
description: The objective and the scope of this scheme is to provide Registration Stamp Duty Subsidy to the eligible Information Technology Units in the State of Goa. All the New and Existing Units having their operations in Goa are eligible. The scheme has been framed as a part of Goa's IT Policy.

name: RKVY Soil Health and Fertility Village level Soil Testing Lab
description: In order to promote soil test analysis in a campaign mode and to create awareness among farmers about soil health for judicious use of chemical fertilisers, organic manure, the component of “Setting of Village-level Soil Testing Laboratories” is being implemented under the scheme.

name: NEC Stipend And Book Grant Scheme
description: This scholarship scheme is offered to the students pursuing higher professional courses and belongs to ST and general category. Only Nagaland domiciled candidates will be eligible to apply for this scheme.

name: State Research Scholarship
description: This scholarship is specially designed for students who are pursuing research work. Under the scheme, beneficiaries will get cash awards to conduct their research work.

name: Partial Travel Support Scheme
description: The Himachal Pradesh Council for Science, Technology & Environment (HIMCOSTE), has a scheme for providing partial travel assistance to deserving bright young Scientists and Research Scholars working in state

name: Widow Pension (CBOCWWB)
description: Under this scheme, financial assistance in the form of a monthly pension shall be given to the widows of male registered construction workers of the Board.

name: Awasiya Vidyala Yojana
description: "Awasiye Vidyala Yojana" initiated by the Labor Department of the Uttar Pradesh State for the education of the construction worker.

name: Grama Jyothi
tags: Grama Jyothi,Mana Ooru Mana Pranalika,Rural Development,Water And Sanitation,Health And Nutrition,Education,Social Security And Poverty Eradication,Natural Resources Management,Agriculture And Infrastructure
category: Agriculture,Rural & Environment,Health & Wellness,Education & Learning,Social welfare & Empowerment,Utility & Sanitation
description: Grama Jyothi is aimed at empowering and improving the standard of living in rural areas through the implementation of various development activities and infrastructure projects. The program focuses on providing basic amenities and services, such as drinking water, sanitation facilities, healthcare.

name: Technical Education Scholarship Scheme for ITI Level
description: The objective of the scheme is to improve the quality of training by attracting promising trainees belonging to Scheduled Caste, Scheduled Tribe & Other Backward Classes & popularize technical training among these categories, so as to make them able to earn their livelihood respectably & honorably.

name: National Fellowship for Students with Disabilities
description: A Scheme "National Fellowship For Students With Disabilities" was initiated by the Department of Empowerment of Persons with Disabilities under the "Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment".

name: Chief Minister’s Yuva Kaushal Yojana
description: The scheme “Chief Minister’s Yuva Kaushal Yojana (CM YKY)” was launched by the government of Arunachal Pradesh on 1st April 2018 to provide high-end training to the youth across the state to enable them to find jobs in the private sector.

name: Hita-dhikaari Ke Samanye Athava Durghatana Me Mrityu Ya Ghayal Hone Ki Dasha Me Sahayata Yojana
description: By the labor department of Rajasthan started "Hita-Dhikaari Ke Samanye Athava Durghatana Me Mrityu Ya Ghayal Hone Ki Dasha Me Sahayata Yojana" for the construction workers.

name: Skill Development Assistance (ANBOCWWB)
tags: Skill Development,Tool Kits,Construction Worker,Building Worker,Labour,Financial Assistance
description: Under this scheme, financial assistance shall be provided to registered construction workers or their two children for the purchase of tool kits upon submission of a successful course/trade completion certificate from a Government Industrial Training Institute or Vocational Training Centre.

name: Indira Gandhi National Widow Pension Scheme-Madhya Pradesh
description: The Indira Gandhi National Widow Pension Scheme is being operated to provide financial support to widowed women living below the poverty line.

name: Scheme of Internship for Post-Graduate/Research Students
description: MoSPI is implementing the scheme of Internship for Post-graduate/Research Students of Statistics/ Mathematical Statistics/ Operations Research/ Economics/ Demography or any of the applied field of Statistics of recognized Universities//Institutions.

name: Ramie Crop Scheme
description: The objective of the scheme is to encourage cultivation of perennial and remunerative textile crop such as Ramie in suitable areas by providing necessary inputs and training.

name: Scheme For Subsidy On Interest For Establishment Of 1 To 20 Milch Animal Farm For Scheduled Caste
description: The scheme “Scheme for Subsidy on Interest for Establishment of 1 to 20 Milch Animal Farm for Scheduled Caste” was started by the Dept. of Agriculture, Farmers Welfare & Co-operation, Government of Gujarat.

name: Mukhyamantri Prakhand Parivahan Yojana
description: "Mukhyamantri Prakhand Parivahan Yojana" to provide transportation facilities connecting blocks & remote Panchayats with district headquarters. This scheme aims to encourage scheduled castes, scheduled tribes, backward classes entrepreneurship by providing financial support to purchase buses.

name: Pradhan Mantri Ujjwala Yojana 2.0
description: Ministry of Petroleum and Natural Gas (MOPNG), introduced the ‘"Pradhan Mantri Ujjawala Yojana 2.0" in India. The Pradhan Mantri Ujjawala Yojana (PMUY) is a scheme launched by the Government of India in 2016 to provide free LPG (liquefied petroleum gas) connections to women from below-poverty-line.

name: National Grassroots Innovation and Outstanding Traditional Knowledge Awards
description: National Innovation Foundation (NIF)-India, an autonomous body of the Department of Science and Technology, Government of India, invites entries of unaided technological innovations and traditional knowledge developed at grassroots by an individual (Citizen of India) or group.

name: Mukhyamantri Arogya Artham Yojana
description: Mukhyamantri Arogya Artham Yojana (MAAY) is a health insurance scheme launched by the government of Gujarat in India. The scheme was launched in September 2012 to provide financial assistance for medical treatment to families living below the poverty line in the state.

name: Udyogini Scheme
category: Social welfare & Empowerment,Business & Entrepreneurship,Women and Child
description: Udyogini is an innovative scheme to assist women in gaining self-reliance and economic independence through self-employment, mainly through trade and the service sector. It also provides for a subsidy on loans for undertaking business activities/ micro enterprises through banks, etc.

name: Integrated Social Security Scheme - Old Age Pension
description: ISSS-OAP is a State Sponsored Scheme by the Social Welfare Dept. of the Govt. of Jammu and Kashmir wherein financial assistance is provided to Old Age Persons who have meager support or no source of livelihood. A pension of ₹1000 per pensioner per month is deposited directly into their Bank Account.

name: National Agriculture Insurance Scheme
description: The National Agricultural Insurance Scheme (NAIS/Rashtriya Krishi Bima Yojana) has been under implementation in Gujarat State since its introduction by the Government of India in the Rabi/Summer 1999-2000 season.

name: Women Involvement in Science and Engineering Research
description: The scheme “Women Involvement in Science and Engineering Research (WISER)” aims to build scientific capacity, retain and promote women researchers in India & Germany by utilizing complementary expertise in science, technology, innovation and research partnerships.

name: Group Personal Accident Insurance Scheme For Coir Workers
category: Banking,Financial Services and Insurance,Social welfare & Empowerment
description: A group insurance scheme by MoMSME for coir workers. The scheme provides insurance cover against accidental death and permanent disability of the insured member.

name: Mukhyamantri Kalakar Sahayata Yojana
description: Mukhyamantri Kalakar Sahayata Yojana is a scheme under the Odia Language, Literature & Culture Department, Government of Odisha aims to offer sustenance and assistance to elderly artists who, despite facing financial hardship, have consistently devoted themselves to enriching culture of the state.

name: National Family Benefit Scheme
description: A family welfare scheme under the umbrella scheme ‘National Social Assistance Programme’ (NSAP) by MoRD. In this scheme, financial assistance is provided to the bereaved households in case of the death of the primary breadwinner irrespective of the cause of death.

name: Assistance to Training Institutions Scheme
description: Under the scheme, assistance would be provided to the training institutions under the Ministry of MSME for creation, strengthening and expansion of infrastructure, including setting-up of new branches and centres.

name: Women’s Instinct for Developing and Ushering in Scientific Heights & Innovation
description: 'WIDUSHI' programme aims to encourage and support senior women scientists to conduct research in interdisciplinary areas of Science and Technology.

name: Generator Subsidy
description: The scheme "Generator Subsidy" is introduced with the objective of assisting all new and existing Micro, Small, and Medium Manufacturing Enterprises through a subsidy of 25% on the cost of the generator purchased (up to 320 KVA capacity), subject to a maximum of ₹ 5,00,000.

name: Old Age Pension Scheme (APB&OCWWB)
description: The scheme “Old Age Pension Scheme” was started by the Department of Labour and Employment, Govt. of Arunachal Pradesh for the registered workers of Arunachal Pradesh Building & Other Construction Workers Welfare Board (APB&OCWWB).

name: Financial Assistance To Inter-Caste Married Couples (Except SC/ST Category)
description: The scheme “Financial Assistance to Inter-Caste Married Couples (Except SC/ST Category)” was launched by the Department of Social Justice, Government of Kerala.

name: Mukhmantri Sehat Bima Yojana
description: "AYUSHMAN BHARAT PM-JAY MUKH MANTRI SEHAT BIMA YOJNA” is a flagship State Health Insurance Program of the Government of Punjab.

name: Deen Dayal Disabled Rehabilitation Scheme
description: The umbrella Central Sector Scheme of this Ministry called the "Scheme to Promote Voluntary Action for Persons with Disabilities" was revised w.e.f. 01.04.2003 and was renamed as the "Deendayal Disabled Rehabilitation Scheme (DDRS)"

name: Kalyana Lakshmi Pathakam
tags: Scheduled Caste,Scheduled Tribe,Backward Class,Economically Backward Class,Marriage
description: The Government of Telangana launched the scheme " Kalyana Lakshmi Pathakam " on 02nd October 2014 for all SC, ST, BC & EBC girls on their marriage with a view to alleviate financial distress in the family.

name: RKVY Soil Health and Fertility - Soil Health Card
description: Soil Health Card is designed to give each farmer soil nutrient status of his/her holding and advice him/her on the dosage of fertilizers and also the needed soil amendments, that s/he should apply to maintain soil health in the long run.

name: Chief Minister Ladli Behna Yojana
description: In 2023, Madhya Pradesh State Government started "Chief Minister Ladli Behna Yojana" for women empowerment

name: Financial Assistance to Brackish Water Aquaculture Farms
description: Through this scheme, financial assistance is provided to eligible fishermen for the construction and renovation of the Farm, for the purchase of farming equipment, and for the purchase of feed. Only the farmers having a water spread area of 2 hectares or less can apply to this scheme.

name: Credit Card Scheme For Artisans And Weavers Of Handicrafts And Handloom Sector
description: The Credit Card Scheme for Artisans & Weavers is a loan scheme by the Department of Handicraft & Handloom (Govt. of Jammu & Kashmir) under which adequate and timely assistance from the financial institutions is provided to the Artisans and Weavers.

name: Nirman Shramikon Ke Bacchon Hetu Nishulk Ganvesh Evam Pustak Copy Hetu Sahaayata Raashi Yojana
description: Chhattisgarh State Government started a scheme "Nirman Shramikon Ke Bacchon Hetu Nishulk Ganvesh Evam Pustak Copy Hetu Sahaayata Raashi Yojana" for construction worker on 09 December 2022.

name: Scheme for Grant of Financial Assistance for Administering Road Safety Advocacy and Awards for the Outstanding Work Done in the Field of Road Safety
description: The objective of the Scheme is to stimulate and encourage opportunities for various agencies through participation, in order to create awareness on road safety.

name: Subsidy Scheme For Establishment Of Goat Unit (10+1) For General Category People
description: The scheme “Subsidy Scheme for Establishment of Goat Unit (10+1) for General Category People” was launched by the Department of Agriculture, Farmers Welfare & Co-operation, Government of Gujarat to uplift Economically poor livestock breeders of Gujarat State.

name: Shree Nanaji Deshmukh Awas Yojana (GBOCWWB)
description: In urban areas, where EWS/LIG houses have been allotted by Local Self-Government Organization/Urban Development Authority & Gujarat Housing Board under Chief Minister/Prime Minister Awas Yojana, the benefit of this scheme is given once per family to construction worker registered in the board.

name: Sanctioning of Tricycles of Orthopedically Challenged
description: The "Sanctioning of Tricycles of Orthopedically Challenged" scheme aims to provide tricycles to orthopedically challenged individuals to enhance their mobility and independence. This initiative ensures that eligible individuals receive the necessary support to lead active and self-reliant lives.

name: Sheep Rearing Scheme (HSFDC)
description: Under this scheme, the Corporation provides loans/benefits to individuals from Below Poverty Line (BPL) families, whose annual family income does not exceed ₹1,80,000/-, in both rural and urban areas for self-employment income generating activities such as sheep rearing.

name: Divyang Boys/ Girls Marriage Incentive Grant
description: “Divyang Youth / Girl Marriage Incentive Grant” is a social security scheme by the Social Welfare Department, Government of Uttarakhand, that provides financial assistance to a couple when a young woman or young man marries a Divyang (person with disability) partner.

name: Grant Scheme for Marriage of Daughters of Destitute Widow
tags: Marriage Grant,Scheduled Caste,Scheduled Tribe,Financial Assistance,Girls,Destitute Widow
description: “Grant Scheme for Marriage of Daughters of Destitute Widow” is a social security scheme by the Social Welfare Department, Government of Uttarakhand, that provides financial assistance to the destitute widows for the marriage of their daughters.

name: Scheme for Conservation and Development of Indigenous Cattle and Murrah Development
description: The scheme is implemented by the Department of Animal Husbandry & Dairying, Government of Haryana with the objective of encouraging the farmers for conservation and development of the indigenous breeds of cows and buffaloes.

name: Incentive Scheme for MSMEs in Powerloom Sector: Work Force Welfare Assistance
description: “Work Force Welfare Assistance” incentive under the “Incentive Scheme for MSMEs in Powerloom Sector” scheme implemented by the Dept. of MSME & T, Government of West Bengal,  aims to provide reimbursement of expenditure incurred for paying contribution towards ESI and EPF.

name: Uttam Pashu Puraskar Yojana
description: The scheme “Uttam Pashu Puraskar Yojana” was launched by the Department of Animal Husbandry, Government of Himachal Pradesh to provide incentives and encouragement to livestock Owners for rearing good quality high yielding animals.

name: Grant of Subsidy for Purchase of Mangalyam to the Bridegroom of Weaker Section
description: The scheme “Grant of Subsidy for Purchase of Mangalyam to the Bridegroom of Weaker Section” by the Dept of Women & Child Development, Govt of Pondicherry, was introduced to provide Financial Assistance of ₹ 2,500/- to the Bridegroom from Weaker Section.

name: Award of Pre-matric Scholarship to the Students Whose Parents Are Engaged in Unclean Occupation
description: "Award of Pre-matric Scholarship to the Students Whose Parents Are Engaged in Unclean Occupation” by the Adi Dravidar Welfare Dept, Govt of Puducherry, provides scholarships to the students whose parents are engaged in unclean occupations to improve the status of the unprivileged society.

name: Asangathita Shramik Sahayika Prakalpa
tags: Unorganised Workers,Social Security,Weaker Section,Unorganized Sectors,Self Employment
description: The Asanghatita Shramik Sahayika Prakalpa (ASSP), a state scheme for the social security of  unorganised workers, has been implemented in Tripura since 2003

name: Mukhyamantri Nirmaan Shramik Dirghayu Sahayata Yojana
description: Chhattisgarh State Government started a scheme "Mukhyamantri Nirmaan Shramik Dirghayu Sahayata Yojana" for Building and other construction worker on 11 January 2012.

name: Punjab Farm Tourism Scheme
description: The scheme envisages to provide to the tourists a clean, hygienic and comfortable stay in the farm houses spread across the State of Punjab. The scheme also aims to provide cultural experience to the domestic and foreign tourists through their exposure to village life.

name: Scheme for Plantation Development (New planting & Replanting) under Medium Term Framework Plan (MTFP) in Traditional Areas (Kerala and Tamil Nadu), Non-Traditional and North Eastern Region
description: The Scheme is intended to increase the production of natural rubber in India by accelerating new planting and replanting of rubber on scientific lines. Accelerated new planting/replanting would be achieved by giving proper technical guidance and financial assistance to growers.

name: Moovalur Ramamirtham Ammaiyar Ninaivu Marriage Assistance Scheme-1
description: In this scheme, ₹ 25,000/- and an 8-gram gold coin is given to brides who have studied Class 10th. This scheme is only applicable for the marriage conducted from 17th May 2011 onwards. The objective of the scheme is to help financially poor parents in getting their daughters mar

name: Accidental Death Benefit Scheme (PBAOCWWB)
description: This scheme extends financial assistance of ₹2,25,000/- to the nominees/dependents of the deceased Construction Worker, apart from the ₹2,00,000/- extended through the Life Insurance Corporation (LIC). The amount is credited through DBT into the bank account of the nominee/dependent.

name: Funeral Benefit (MBOCWWB)
description: Under the scheme, financial assistance of ₹5,000/- shall be provided to nominees or dependents of deceased registered construction workers, towards funeral expenses.

name: Old Age Pension Scheme under Chief  Minister’s Uzhavar Padhukappu Thittam
description: The 'Old Age Pension Scheme under Chief Minister’s Uzhavar Padhukappu Thittam' is a state scheme. The scheme aims to give a pension of ₹1,000/- to old-age farmers and destitute agricultural labourers who have membership card under CMPUT.

name: Honorarium for Pradhan Samajpatis of Indigenous Tribal Community
description: “Honorarium for Pradhan Samajpatis of Indigenous Tribal Community" was launched by the Directorate of Social Welfare and Social Education, Govt. of Tripura on 1st July 2021 to provide financial assistance to to the Pradhan Samajpatis (Chief Community Headman) of indigenous tribal community.

name: Mukhyamantri Samajik Sahayata Prakalpa - Unorganized Workers
description: The scheme “Mukhyamantri Samajik Sahayata Prakalpa-Unorganized Workers" was launched by the Directorate of Social Welfare and Social Education, Government of Tripura. The objective of this scheme is to provide financial benefits to Unorganized Workers (home-based, self-employed or wage workers).

name: Maternity Benefit Scheme (UKBOCWWB)
description: Under the scheme, financial assistance is provided to women registered construction workers during the maternity period, subject to the conditions specified by the Board. This assistance will only be provided upon the birth of two children.

name: Rashtriya Vigyan Puraskar
description: The objective of the Rashtriya Vigyan Puraskar (RVP) is to recognise the notable and inspiring contribution made by the scientists, technologists and innovators individually or in teams in various fields of science, technology and technology- led innovation.

name: Fruit Processing Centre
description: The objective of scheme is to disseminate technical knowhow to youth entrepreneurs, farmers & housewives through practical demonstration on importance of fruit preservation & to manufacture quality processed fruit products such as Squashes, Jams, Jelly & Juices under trade name ‘Meg Fruits Product'.

name: Assistance Scheme For Reimbursement For Expenditure On Visa By Construction Workers For Employment Abroad
description: This scheme will be called "Reimbursement of expenditure incurred on visa for employment abroad to construction workers". The purpose of this scheme is to provide assistance to the registered beneficiaries employed in building and other construction works for better employment opportunities.

name: Delhi Family Benefit Scheme
description: Family Benefit Scheme (NFBS) to assist those Below Poverty Line (BPL) families whose alone bread earner expires due to natural or accidental causes.

name: Nirman Shramik Safety Kit Yojana
description: "Nirman Shramik Safety Kit Yojana" is a scheme by the Department of Labour, Employment, Training & Skill Development Govt of Jharkhand. The scheme provides a direct cash transfer of ₹ 1,000/- for purchasing a branded helmet and a pair of safety shoes.

name: Startup Manipur
description: The state government of Manipur has introduced the 'Startup Manipur' initiative, aimed at promoting sustainable economic development and generating significant employment opportunities in the region.

name: Co-Working Space/ Incubators/ Accelerators Subsidy Scheme
description: The scheme “Co-Working Space/ Incubators/ Accelerators Subsidy Scheme” is a scheme by the Dept. of Information Technology, Electronics and Communications, Govt. of Goa, for the Startups of Goa. Through this scheme, the startups will be reimbursed a fixed amount for the seats occupied by them.

name: Scheme of Grant-in-Aid to Voluntary Organisations Working for the Welfare of Scheduled Tribes
description: The Central Sector Scheme “Scheme of Grant-in-Aid to Voluntary Organisations Working for the Welfare of Scheduled Tribes” was launched by the Ministry of Tribal Affairs, Government of India.

name: Mukhya Mantri Shahri Ajeevika Guarantee Yojna
description: The “Mukhya Mantri Shahri Ajeevika Guarantee Yojna” was launched by the Department of Urban Development, Govt. of Himachal Pradesh. The objective of the scheme is to enhance livelihood security in urban areas by providing 120 days of guaranteed wage employment to every household in a financial year.

name: Grant of Subsidy for Purchase of Mobile Sea Food Van
description: The scheme aims to provide the beneficiary with a mobile seafood van. This van, financed through a combination of bank loan and departmental subsidy (25% and 75%, respectively), is intended for the sale of fresh and processed fish and fishery products in areas not served by regular markets.

name: Lean Season Assistance under "Welfare and Relief for Fishermen During Lean Seasons and Natural Calamities Scheme"
description: The scheme "Lean Season Assistance" under "Welfare and Relief for Fishermen During Lean Seasons and Natural Calamities Scheme" is introduced with the objective of assisting fishermen families who are deprived of income during natural calamities and fishing ban periods.

name: Baristha Nagarika Tirtha Yatra Yojana
description: The scheme “Baristha Nagarika Tirtha Yatra Yojana” was launched by the Department of Tourism, Government of Odisha on 01st February 2016 in collaboration with IRCTC to help senior citizens over 60-75 years of age to undertake pilgrimage with Government assistance.

name: Paired Early Career Fellowship in Applied Research
description: PECFAR is a fellowship to facilitate a two-way exchange of young early-career Indian and German researchers through short visits for networking and exploring avenues for collaboration and innovation in applied research.

name: Promotion of Literature on Art & Culture of Local Authors/ Organization
description: The scheme "Goa State Best Library and Best Librarian Award" has been designed to encourage Goan writers to publish their literature on Art and Culture. The entire expenditure on printing and publishing the book is borne by Govt. by keeping the copyright of the publication.

name: Kerala Biotechnology Re-Entry Fellowship
description: “Kerala Biotechnology Re-Entry Fellowship (K-BiREF)” is a fellowship programme to attract well-trained and highly skilled researchers with a good track record (Indian nationals) working abroad in various frontier areas in biotechnology to research and academic institutions in Kerala.

name: Computer Training Scheme
description: The scheme is being operated with the objective to provide better chances of employment to the youth by enhancing their skills.

name: National Handicrafts Development Programme: Infrastructure And Technology Support: EMPORIA
description: In the scheme "Infrastructure and Technology Support: EMPORIA" assistance would be provided for the setting up of emporia. These would be set up in commercially viable locations in the implementing agencies' own/rented buildings.

name: Journalist's Medical Welfare Scheme - Assam
description: The Journalist's Medical Welfare Scheme was first implemented in 2012 by the Government of Assam. Under this scheme, one-time financial assistance is provided to the accredited and recognized journalists of Assam for their medical treatment.

name: State Marriage Assistance Scheme For Poor Girls
description: A social welfare scheme by the Social Welfare Department of the Government of Jammu & Kashmir, for Poor Girls of Marriageable Age who belong to either AAY (Antyodaya Anna Yojana) or PHH (Priority Households) ration card holder families. The scheme is operational in all the districts across the UT.

name: OEC Pre-matric Educational Assistance
description: The Scheme “OEC Pre-matric Educational Assistance” was started by the Backward Classes Development Department, Government of Kerala to provide educational assistance to pre-matric students belonging to these communities who are studying in Government/Aided/Unaided schools from Classes 1st to 10th.

name: Coffee Development Programme in North Eastern Region: Quality Upgradation / Certification: Drying Yards
description: The scheme "Quality Upgradation / Certification: Drying Yards" aims to facilitate the improvement of the quality of coffee produced by growers by encouraging them to establish infrastructure for quality enhancement and obtain certification for their coffees, enabling them to earn better returns.

name: SERB - POWER Research Grants
description: The aim of the ‘SERB - POWER Research Grants’ is to encourage emerging and eminent women researchers for individual-centric and competitive mode of research funding to undertake R&D activities in frontier areas of science and engineering.

name: Nekar Samman Yojana
description: In 2020 amidst the Covid pandemic, Chief Minister of Karnataka launched a mega scheme Karnataka Nekar Samman Yojana. It was a relief scheme to provide financial support to destitute weaver of state engaged in the handloom and textile industry whose livelihood was adversely affected by the pandemic.

name: Solar Power Subsidy Scheme
description: Launched in 2018, the "Solar Power Subsidy Scheme" is one of the "Information Technology Policy Schemes" by the Department of Information Technology, Government of Goa. The objective and the scope of this scheme is to provide Solar Power Subsidy to the eligible Information Technology Units in Goa.

name: Health Minister’s Discretionary Grant
description: A health scheme by Ministry of Health & Family Welfare for financially poor patients to defray a part of the expenditure on Hospitalization/treatment in Government Hospitals,for life threatening diseases covered under Rashtriya Arogya Nidhi (RAN), in cases where free medical facilities aren't there.

name: State Merit Scholarship Manipur
description: The Directorate of University & Higher Education, Manipur is interested in awarding State Merit Scholarships to meritorious students of Manipur through online application submissions to promote higher education for economically weaker students in the state.

name: Payroll Subsidy
description: The scheme "Payroll Subsidy" by the Govt of Tamil Nadu, is introduced with the objective of assisting MSMEs in reducing their employee cost. The scheme provides reimbursement of employee's contributions to the EPF for their employees, subject to a maximum of ₹ 24,000/- per employee per annum.

name: RMEWF-Financial Assistance For Vocational Training Of Widows Of Ex-Servicemen
description: A scheme to provide financial assistance to a widow of Ex-Servicemen to settle in life through vocational training.

name: Domestic Funding Of Foreign Training
description: The scheme "Domestic Funding of Foreign Training (DFFT)" is a scheme introduced by the Department of Personnel and Training, Government of India in the year 2001-02 with an objective to upgrade the knowledge & skills of Government officers.

name: Krishak Durghatna Kalyan Yojana
description: The government will provide compensation to the farmers after any accident.

name: Samruddhi Scheme
category: Social welfare & Empowerment,Business & Entrepreneurship,Women and Child
description: Samruddhi scheme is an initiative from the Social Welfare Department of Government of Karnataka. It serves as an enabler to the socially disadvantaged youth and women to take up entrepreneurial activities and promote self-employment.

name: Scheme For Assistance For Start Ups/ Innovation
description: The "Scheme for Assistance for Startups / Innovation" has been introduced to encourage R&D and start innovation and entrepreneurship at different levels of the startup cycle. The scheme came into force on 07/08/2020 and will remain in operation for a period of 5 years, i.e. upto 06.08.2025.

name: Entrepreneur Support Scheme
description: Entrepreneur Support Scheme (ESS) is the most popular & attractive scheme operated by the Directorate of Industries and Commerce.The scheme aims to provide financial assistance to Micro,Small&Medium Enterprises engaged in manufacturing activities in the State,proportional to capital investment made.

name: AICTE-National Initiative for Training of Technical Teachers (for Inductee Teachers) Scheme
description: Ministry of Human Resource Development (MHRD) and All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE) jointly proposed an initiative called “National Initiative for Technical Teachers Training (NITTT)” to address the technical teachers of the country who plays an active role in the technical education

name: International Cooperation Scheme- Capacity Building of First Time MSE Exporters
description: The scheme “International Cooperation Scheme” was launched by the MSME, Govt. of India with the aim to capacity build MSMEs for entering export market by providing reimbursement of various costs incurred by first time MSE exporters on export shipments.

name: Samagra Samajik Suraksha Parityakta Pension Yojana
description: Under the Scheme, Madhya Pradesh government provides financial benefits to Be from a family living below the poverty line.

name: Integrated Technology Enabled Agriculture Management System Or iTEAMS
description: The scheme was launched by the Department of Agriculture & Farmers’ Welfare, Govt. of Meghalaya to address critical issues of enabling & facilitating access to remunerative & sustainable markets for farmers produce in most transparent & effective manner through facilitation service iTEAM Dial 1917.

name: National Awards For Outstanding Services In The Field Of Prevention Of Alcoholism And Substance (Drug) Abuse: Outstanding Achievement By An Individual
description: To recognize the efforts, and, encourage excellence in the Prevention of Alcoholism and Substance (Drugs) Abuse and the rehabilitation of its victims, awards will be presented for the most effective or outstanding services in the prevention of Alcoholism and Substance (Drug) Abuse.

name: Stipend For Girls Of Secondary Students Schemes
description: The Nagaland Stipend for Girls of Secondary Students scheme is a scholarship program launched by the Government of Nagaland with the aim of promoting and encouraging girl students to continue their education beyond the secondary level.

name: Stand-Up India
category: Business & Entrepreneurship,Banking,Financial Services and Insurance,Social welfare & Empowerment
description: A scheme by Ministry of Finance for financing SC/ST and  Women Entrepreneurs by facilitating bank loans for setting up a greenfield project  Enterprise in manufacturing, services, trading sector and activities allied to agriculture.

name: Skill Loan Scheme
